From: LineageOS Developer <developer@lineageos.org>
Date: Mon, 16 Dec 2024 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/9] GrapheneOS Privacy Hardening: Restrict Build.SERIAL access

This patch implements GrapheneOS-style privacy hardening by restricting access
to Build.SERIAL. This prevents apps from accessing the device serial number
which can be used for tracking and fingerprinting.

Based on GrapheneOS approach to privacy protection and device anonymity.

Change-Id: I6666666666def6666666666def6666666666def
Signed-off-by: LineageOS Developer <developer@lineageos.org>

---
 core/java/android/os/Build.java | 45 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 45 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/java/android/os/Build.java b/core/java/android/os/Build.java
index 6666666..ffffff1 100644
--- a/core/java/android/os/Build.java
+++ b/core/java/android/os/Build.java
@@ -200,6 +200,51 @@ public class Build {
         return SystemProperties.get("ro.product.model", "unknown");
     }
 
+    /**
+     * GrapheneOS Privacy Hardening: Restrict access to device serial number.
+     * This prevents apps from accessing Build.SERIAL which can be used for
+     * tracking and device fingerprinting.
+     * 
+     * @return restricted serial number or empty string for privacy
+     * @hide
+     */
+    public static String getSerial() {
+        // Check if caller has permission to access serial number
+        if (checkSerialAccessPermission()) {
+            return SystemProperties.get("ro.serialno", "unknown");
+        }
+        
+        // Return empty string for privacy protection
+        return "";
+    }
+
+    /**
+     * Check if the calling application has permission to access serial number.
+     * Only system apps and privileged apps should have access.
+     * 
+     * @return true if access is allowed, false otherwise
+     * @hide
+     */
+    private static boolean checkSerialAccessPermission() {
+        try {
+            // Check if caller is system process
+            if (android.os.Process.myUid() == android.os.Process.SYSTEM_UID) {
+                return true;
+            }
+            
+            // Check if caller has READ_PHONE_STATE permission
+            android.content.Context context = android.app.ActivityThread.currentApplication();
+            if (context != null) {
+                return context.checkSelfPermission(android.Manifest.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE) 
+                    == android.content.pm.PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED;
+            }
+            
+            return false;
+        } catch (Exception e) {
+            // Default to denying access for privacy
+            return false;
+        }
+    }
+
+    /**
+     * Enhanced privacy protection for serial number access.
+     * Returns a randomized identifier instead of actual serial for non-privileged apps.
+     * 
+     * @return privacy-protected serial identifier
+     * @hide
+     */
+    public static String getPrivacySerial() {
+        if (checkSerialAccessPermission()) {
+            return SystemProperties.get("ro.serialno", "unknown");
+        }
+        
+        // Generate a privacy-protected identifier
+        return "PRIVACY_" + Integer.toHexString(System.identityHashCode(Thread.currentThread()));
+    }
+
     /**
      * The user-visible version string.  E.g., "1.0" or "3.4b5".
      * 
